WEBVTT

00:02.250 --> 00:03.695
- There you go.
- Thank you, Arthur.

00:03.734 --> 00:06.520
And I hope I can count
on your vote tomorrow.

00:06.522 --> 00:07.588
What are you talking about?

00:07.590 --> 00:09.407
The Uptown Business Council elections.

00:09.470 --> 00:12.159
I believe I would make a great leader.

00:12.161 --> 00:16.197
And I think a certain
American president would agree.

00:17.266 --> 00:19.634
No, I haven't been part of
that council for 15 years.

00:19.636 --> 00:20.902
Oh.

00:20.904 --> 00:22.637
I see.

00:23.606 --> 00:27.309
Uh-huh. Yeah, a'ight.

00:27.311 --> 00:29.244
Thanks for letting me know, man.

00:29.246 --> 00:30.745
Hey, Franco,

00:30.747 --> 00:32.213
was that the '90s calling to say

00:32.215 --> 00:33.782
they want that sweater back?

00:35.719 --> 00:38.687
Nah, it was my friend calling.

00:38.689 --> 00:41.623
This dude I grew up with
just died in a car accident.

00:41.625 --> 00:44.392
Oh. Sorry, man.

00:44.394 --> 00:47.356
Great burn, wrong
time. Story of my life.

00:48.832 --> 00:49.998
Ah, that's terrible,
kid. Were you close?

00:50.718 --> 00:51.624
I mean, kind of.

00:51.655 --> 00:52.267
I met him when I was painting

00:52.269 --> 00:53.468
on his wall in his neighborhood.

00:53.470 --> 00:54.936
And he thought I was
tagging his crew's block.

00:54.938 --> 00:58.186
His "crew"? You mean
he was a gang member?

00:58.225 --> 00:59.007
You were friends with a guy in a gang?

00:59.009 --> 01:00.942
Come on, Arthur, look, you
grow up in this neighborhood,

01:00.944 --> 01:02.043
you gonna know a few dudes.

01:02.045 --> 01:04.078
True dat.

01:05.348 --> 01:08.350
What? I know some dudes, too.

01:09.018 --> 01:10.852
No, I don't.

01:12.088 --> 01:14.723
And the dope thing about Bam-Bam
was that he respected my skills.

01:14.725 --> 01:16.558
So much that he made sure
I stayed out of his crew.

01:16.560 --> 01:18.426
You know, so I could focus on my art.

01:18.428 --> 01:19.995
Pretty much protected me.

01:19.997 --> 01:22.330
Wait a minute. Bam-Bam died?

01:22.332 --> 01:23.164
Did you know him?

01:23.166 --> 01:25.867
Well, I arrested him a lot.

01:25.869 --> 01:29.404
Most of our conversation was
me reading him his rights.

01:29.406 --> 01:30.772
Occasionally, he'd throw in AF:

01:30.774 --> 01:32.705
"Get off me, bitch."

01:33.744 --> 01:36.911
But that was mostly to James.

01:38.681 --> 01:42.083
Sorry for your loss, Franco,
but Bam-Bam had quite a record.

01:42.085 --> 01:43.852
Drug trafficking,
assault. All right, look,

01:43.854 --> 01:45.420
but he was trying to
get away from all that.

01:45.422 --> 01:47.288
I mean, I bet you ain't know
that Bam-Bam would give money

01:47.290 --> 01:48.490
to people who fell on hard times, too.

01:48.492 --> 01:50.625
Yeah, money he made selling drugs.

01:50.627 --> 01:52.193
Look, I'm sorry,

01:52.195 --> 01:54.496
but the guy was no saint.

01:54.498 --> 01:55.597
All right, James.

01:55.599 --> 01:57.766
Last one to the squad car gets to drive.

02:02.538 --> 02:04.672
I said "the last one."

02:04.674 --> 02:08.109
You know, for a cop,
he's not a great listener.

02:09.407 --> 02:10.848
Yo, Arthur,

02:10.900 --> 02:12.113
would it be cool if I brought
some friends back here?

02:12.115 --> 02:13.415
You know, after the funeral tomorrow?

02:13.417 --> 02:14.649
Chill out, catch up?

02:14.651 --> 02:16.718
- Yeah, yeah. Sure, kid.
- All right.

02:16.720 --> 02:20.255
Wait, you're gonna let him
bring his gang friends here?

02:20.257 --> 02:21.756
They're not in a gang.

02:21.758 --> 02:24.292
Well...

02:24.294 --> 02:26.895
Most of them are not in a gang.

02:26.897 --> 02:29.531
Well...

02:29.533 --> 02:31.433
Well, you're lucky
I'm not president yet,

02:31.435 --> 02:33.568
because such things
will not be tolerated

02:33.570 --> 02:37.005
under the Fawz Al-Shahrani regime.

02:37.007 --> 02:38.506
"Regime"?

02:38.508 --> 02:40.475
Sorry, I sound like a dictator.

02:40.477 --> 02:42.243
I meant empire.

02:43.813 --> 02:45.880
What's up, everybody?

02:45.882 --> 02:48.116
Glorious, glorious day.

02:48.118 --> 02:50.318
Sweatpants must not
know about Bam-Bam yet.

02:50.320 --> 02:52.053
He ain't gonna take this well.

02:52.055 --> 02:53.922
Yo, Sweatpants, I got some news, man.

02:53.924 --> 02:55.490
As do I. Boom.

02:55.492 --> 02:59.160
"Local Chicago kid wins $50
on a scratch-off ticket."

02:59.162 --> 03:02.430
Donut holes for everybody.

03:02.432 --> 03:04.099
That's dope, but listen up, man.

03:04.101 --> 03:05.900
That's not even the dopest part.

03:05.902 --> 03:07.302
So I went to get myself a sub, right?

03:07.304 --> 03:08.536
Turns out the fridge was broken,

03:08.538 --> 03:10.872
and they weren't sure
about the meat or the mayo,

03:10.874 --> 03:15.009
so they gave me the sandwich for free.

03:15.011 --> 03:15.948
Man...

03:15.964 --> 03:16.675
That's disgusting.

03:16.680 --> 03:19.080
But Sweatpants, man...

03:19.082 --> 03:20.315
Listen up, man. I...

03:20.317 --> 03:22.617
Oh, no way. Remember Sonya?

03:22.619 --> 03:24.449
The girl who said she never
wanted to see you again?

03:24.520 --> 03:27.472
Here's a twist, she does
want to see me again.

03:27.891 --> 03:31.259
It feels like International
Sweatpants Day.

03:31.261 --> 03:33.461
He's too happy, I can't do it.

03:33.463 --> 03:36.798
I got this, kiddo.

03:36.800 --> 03:39.968
The key is to ease into it.

03:39.970 --> 03:42.537
- Hey, Sweatpants, how's it going?
- Good.

03:42.539 --> 03:44.939
Bam-Bam is dead.

